No sorry, something like:-
{
  "fields": {
                   "running": false,
                   "conveyorStop": true,
                    ......
                },
  "timestamp": 1600002002020
}

So that the user defined fields are separate to the timestamp field. This way the user can add a tag 'timestamp' and not have to worry about conflicting with the timestamp field. It also allows us to add optional fields in the future without having to worry about conflicting with peoples user defined fields.
